Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip.
Production date: 148 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Pythogenes. Similar die to Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0200.33 Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0969)
